-url\", dialogUrl,\n            \"--user\", \"SA\",\n            \"--password\", \"\",\n            \"--noexit\"\n        });\n\n        assertThat(ConnectionDialogTestDriver.constructorInvocations()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(ConnectionDialogTestDriver.connectInvocations()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(databaseManagerFrame()).isNotNull();\n        try (Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(realUrl + \";ifexists=true\", \"SA\", \"\")) {\n            assertThat(connection.isValid(2)).isTrue();\n        } finally {\n            closeOpenWindows();\n        }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static void closeOpenWindows() {\n        for (Window window : Window.getWindows()) {\n            if (window instanceof Frame) {\n                Frame frame = (Frame) window;\n\n                if (isDatabaseManagerFrame(frame)) {\n                    frame.dispatchEvent(new WindowEvent(frame, WindowEvent.WINDOW_CLOSING));\n                    frame.dispose();\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}", "newText": "    private static void closeOpenWindows() {\n        for (Window window : Window.getWindows()) {\n            if (window instanceof Frame) {\n                Frame frame = (Frame) window;\n\n                if (isDatabaseManagerFrame(frame)) {\n                    frame.dispatchEvent(new WindowEvent(frame, WindowEvent.WINDOW_CLOSING));\n                    frame.dispose();\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class ConnectionDialogTestDriver implements Driver {\n        private static final AtomicInteger CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\n        private static final AtomicInteger CONNECT_INVOCATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\n\n        static {\n            try {\n                DriverManager.registerDriver(new ConnectionDialogTestDriver(false));\n            } catch (SQLException exception) {\n                throw new ExceptionInInitializerError(exception);\n            }\n        }\n\n        public ConnectionDialogTestDriver() {\n            this(true);\n        }\n\n        private ConnectionDialogTestDriver(boolean countInvocation) {\n            if (countInvocation) {\n                CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.incrementAndGet();\n            }\n        }\n\n        static void reset() {\n            CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.set(0);\n            CONNECT_INVOCATIONS.set(0);\n        }\n\n        static int constructorInvocations() {\n            return CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.get();\n        }\n\n        static int connectInvocations() {\n            return CONNECT_INVOCATIONS.get();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Connection connect(String url, Properties info) throws SQLException {\n            if (!acceptsURL(url)) {\n                return null;\n            }\n\n            CONNECT_INVOCATIONS.incrementAndGet();\n\n            return new JDBCDriver().connect(url.substring(URL_PREFIX.length()), info);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean acceptsURL(String url) {\n            return url != null && url.startsWith(URL_PREFIX);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public DriverPropertyInfo[] getPropertyInfo(String url, Properties info) {\n            return new DriverPropertyInfo[0];\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getMajorVersion() {\n            return 1;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getMinorVersion() {\n            return 0;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean jdbcCompliant() {\n            return false;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Logger getParentLogger() throws SQLFeatureNotSupportedException {\n            throw new SQLFeatureNotSupportedException();\n        }\n    }\n}"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing test implementation issues**\n\nI’m looking into the test implementation regarding the debug jar and how it affects the classifier not matching the exact artifact, which seems off. There could be duplicate classes if the library jars include both the regular and debug versions. I think dependency substitution might help, but not sure. Also, there are concerns about reporting if the tool can't mark due to an unknown source. I wonder if a more focused test using MethodHandles could clarify things.\n\n**Evaluating validation and testing**\n\nI'm considering if I could remove the validation from DriverManager to cut down on extra dynamic issues, but that doesn't seem right. I might use `DatabaseManager.main` with the default driver `org.hsqldb.jdbcDriver` and `--script`, but I'm not convinced that's the solution either. Updating the build.gradle to include JaCoCo for non-location classes is another thought, though it seems dynamic coverage might not apply. Maybe adding a source file for `ConnectionDialog.java` in test resources could help?\n\n**Exploring API testing**\n\nI'm considering testing a public API without using an actual database, while still going through AWT. I think avoiding HSQLDB could simplify things. I might need to auto connect before establishing the main connection. I'm pondering whether I should add a custom inner class or if the test top-level class requires public access. The naming conventions seem a bit tricky, especially with the `$` in class names, but I feel like it's okay for my setup.\n\n**Evaluating metadata conditions**\n\nI'm thinking that conditional metadata might be acceptable in a Native context. But what if the metadata is absent under native runtime? Actually, it looks like the metadata gets generated and merged. I should run a test. Also, I noticed that the dynamic inner class uses a public no-arg constructor, which makes me wonder if the inner test class should be a public static class. There’s a lot to untangle here!\n\n**Evaluating connection handling**\n\nI'm considering the DriverManager's behavior and how it handles the same inputs across the board. I can accept if there's a prefix, but for the delegate, I might need to replace that prefix. I'm also questioning the getPropertyInfo method for the delegate. If it doesn't work, I won't bother. There seems to be an exception regarding SQLFeatureNotSupported that needs attention. I'll double-check the DatabaseManager.connect method as it uses meta and refreshTree—time to tidy up and edit the test now!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0413721a0db94a26016a1187fe3da8819fb72231008b1650f2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEYgmQ_sfjUsJewGwJukyr-629qWuimzZa4cGWmXkoEoaklep1h-3jRX0fNCp33CKvJk7HJ6lkRLp1A7vhzXT87CymWrvIwiwX719DkHEEXYDOvdgYcz7A_uBO-lPm7WiTOIJ_541N0jVsdSKCrwNr92hC9OH9CMSTFGe0mKDYRmSoUTGC_hv6yKr-aCSFX0VI6GYw2WwIFmxUQQ9ErI1ShRkuUXi0KL484KHu6X3CvS8eOy_1t-1Ji9yBGFWmzExtXegDZFLmGQIDbDhKAxAzFFkO0_4P6SeldKnJ7dUGEoiOsniPEU7mdRrCwNs8fIbbTrK3MnzwGVUohBZjSuA60J5gCqu4NjfJRxkKKiZCHEQD8fIi5z__LnRqPXYJRuwFsGlrlVDsH_VbGTW4cVu0zau1URpp-s1UWLKSjirvvABojtbGsSL54HJEzkTC0mHfC_lwGTuW7YxLrXo7AexPpb6sxZq632FiZm-9_SVScMh1dH5StyshpXtWnw8zcZkR-3Bk2K4H6RJGGXtu55EnQHhP-mtZtVe0yjbhhG2FHjmEi8vZo2xJXiuS2dkR3Y0Lp7qw2-mATv09Hhfe20QSyas9VIwr2fB3KMpwabaoXYrzL8rxP08tCjDg32DjSHIa83jvXLKT0QdjPaSWb_VkGZX4DiNlgEOCefSUrlSMjUNJ4MEvPr92zRsGwp1aoTdFJxWA0jqcb2068s-FfC41oOSUaTqxvPaVqKOMDu_bCAanb4mGBbXcs3YiOnkzFCJBf2tYgumuFglyUbAZzx5e2M2Mm9l9T4beSw8R21OGd37h2V3sqOQuZUDVz91fYCsfs2xrL48PtV_ieZRUFOotUIwB0MPB1WYnC2enNFm7xmHNlyHOyqGYueN-Gr_lKrt4OIq1FyvEofOsdVWugp-0Yc9UMu41A-s6GeYkU5fZD-v8i2Z2jtgs8LQGojMXKkfpSDglEVqJNMiacvHVhNyqk3SumjRQ_hThBOFK-qvtJixZ7zvrRM-tE-cchO0Nua1J19z0BL5Y4KbnEM7iEOg722S-jz-5JGkHeo2cBMwTGv4S019w8ZWBLpkN46iK9EXKHbVgFX1qTYGtJPzCI1GaXgXId07I5K0VQ__lKmFTU1ZLpuBpPQfl6Q2Mti1Tic_mdyxKk3A9Tu3NcXaFhfFY-E9XvLAR70LOcwHtsaZGCI0Sw9s