ot sure. Also, there are concerns about reporting if the tool can't mark due to an unknown source. I wonder if a more focused test using MethodHandles could clarify things.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating validation and testing**\\n\\nI'm considering if I could remove the validation from DriverManager to cut down on extra dynamic issues, but that doesn't seem right. I might use `DatabaseManager.main` with the default driver `org.hsqldb.jdbcDriver` and `--script`, but I'm not convinced that's the solution either. Updating the build.gradle to include JaCoCo for non-location classes is another thought, though it seems dynamic coverage might not apply. Maybe adding a source file for `ConnectionDialog.java` in test resources could help?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring API testing**\\n\\nI'm considering testing a public API without using an actual database, while still going through AWT. I think avoiding HSQLDB could simplify things. I might need to auto connect before establishing the main connection. I'm pondering whether I should add a custom inner class or if the test top-level class requires public access. The naming conventions seem a bit tricky, especially with the `$` in class names, but I feel like it's okay for my setup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating metadata conditions**\\n\\nI'm thinking that conditional metadata might be acceptable in a Native context. But what if the metadata is absent under native runtime? Actually, it looks like the metadata gets generated and merged. I should run a test. Also, I noticed that the dynamic inner class uses a public no-arg constructor, which makes me wonder if the inner test class should be a public static class. There’s a lot to untangle here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating connection handling**\\n\\nI'm considering the DriverManager's behavior and how it handles the same inputs across the board. I can accept if there's a prefix, but for the delegate, I might need to replace that prefix. I'm also questioning the getPropertyInfo method for the delegate. If it doesn't work, I won't bother. There seems to be an exception regarding SQLFeatureNotSupported that needs attention. I'll double-check the DatabaseManager.connect method as it uses meta and refreshTree—time to tidy up and edit the test now!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_OXL2xWfW2evetXZJmj24pS58|fc_0413721a0db94a26016a1188268888819f8baf6d498c55d814", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/ConnectionDialogTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.sql.Connection;\nimport java.sql.DriverManager;\n\nimport org.hsqldb.util.DatabaseManager;\n", "newText": "import java.sql.Connection;\nimport java.sql.Driver;\nimport java.sql.DriverManager;\nimport java.sql.DriverPropertyInfo;\nimport java.sql.SQLException;\nimport java.sql.SQLFeatureNotSupportedException;\nimport java.util.Properties;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\n\nimport org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCDriver;\nimport org.hsqldb.util.DatabaseManager;\n"}, {"oldText": "public class ConnectionDialogTest {\n    private static final String DRIVER_CLASS_NAME = \"org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCDriver\";\n", "newText": "public class ConnectionDialogTest {\n    private static final String DRIVER_CLASS_NAME = ConnectionDialogTestDriver.class.getName();\n    private static final String URL_PREFIX = \"jdbc:connectiondialog:\";\n"}, {"oldText": "        String url = \"jdbc:hsqldb:mem:\" + databaseName;\n\n        DatabaseManager.main(new String[] {\n            \"--driver\", DRIVER_CLASS_NAME,\n            \"--url\", url,\n            \"--user\", \"SA\",\n            \"--password\", \"\",\n            \"--noexit\"\n        });\n\n        assertThat(databaseManagerFrame()).isNotNull();\n        try (Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(url + \";ifexists=true\", \"SA\", \"\")) {\n            assertThat(connection.isValid(2)).isTrue();\n        } finally {\n            closeOpenWindows();\n        }\n", "newText": "        String realUrl = \"jdbc:hsqldb:mem:\" + databaseName;\n        String dialogUrl = URL_PREFIX + realUrl;\n        ConnectionDialogTestDriver.reset();\n\n        DatabaseManager.main(new String[] {\n            \"--driver\", DRIVER_CLASS_NAME,\n            \"--url\", dialogUrl,\n            \"--user\", \"SA\",\n            \"--password\", \"\",\n            \"--noexit\"\n        });\n\n        assertThat(ConnectionDialogTestDriver.constructorInvocations()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(ConnectionDialogTestDriver.connectInvocations()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(databaseManagerFrame()).isNotNull();\n        try (Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(realUrl + \";ifexists=true\", \"SA\", \"\")) {\n            assertThat(connection.isValid(2)).isTrue();\n        } finally {\n            closeOpenWindows();\n        }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static void closeOpenWindows() {\n        for (Window window : Window.getWindows()) {\n            if (window instanceof Frame) {\n                Frame frame = (Frame) window;\n\n                if (isDatabaseManagerFrame(frame)) {\n                    frame.dispatchEvent(new WindowEvent(frame, WindowEvent.WINDOW_CLOSING));\n                    frame.dispose();\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}", "newText": "    private static void closeOpenWindows() {\n        for (Window window : Window.getWindows()) {\n            if (window instanceof Frame) {\n                Frame frame = (Frame) window;\n\n                if (isDatabaseManagerFrame(frame)) {\n                    frame.dispatchEvent(new WindowEvent(frame, WindowEvent.WINDOW_CLOSING));\n                    frame.dispose();\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class ConnectionDialogTestDriver implements Driver {\n        private static final AtomicInteger CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\n        private static final AtomicInteger CONNECT_INVOCATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\n\n        static {\n            try {\n                DriverManager.registerDriver(new ConnectionDialogTestDriver(false));\n            } catch (SQLException exception) {\n                throw new ExceptionInInitializerError(exception);\n            }\n        }\n\n        public ConnectionDialogTestDriver() {\n            this(true);\n        }\n\n        private ConnectionDialogTestDriver(boolean countInvocation) {\n            if (countInvocation) {\n                CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.incrementAndGet();\n            }\n        }\n\n        static void reset() {\n            CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.set(0);\n            CONNECT_INVOCATIONS.set(0);\n        }\n\n        static int constructorInvocations() {\n            return CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.get();\n        }\n\n        static int connectInvocations() {\n            return CONNECT_INVOCATIONS.get();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Connection connect(String url, Properties info) throws SQLException {\n            if (!acceptsURL(url)) {\n                return null;\n            }\n\n            CONNECT_INVOCATIONS.incrementAndGet();\n\n            return new JDBCDriver().connect(url.substring(URL_PREFIX.length()), info);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean acceptsURL(String url) {\n            return url != null && url.startsWith(URL_PREFIX);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public DriverPropertyInfo[] getPropertyInfo(String url, Properties info) {\n            return new DriverPropertyInfo[0];\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getMajorVersion() {\n            return 1;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getMinorVersion() {\n            return 0;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean jdbcCompliant() {\n            return false;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Logger getParentLogger() throws SQLFeatureNotSupportedException {\n            throw new SQLFeatureNotSupportedException();\n        }\n    }\n}"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 693, "output": 3923, "cacheRead": 50688, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55304, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779533819455, "responseId": "resp_0413721a0db94a26016a1187fdac30819fa849d3180864672b"}}
