e’re missing something in our explanation. \\n\\nThe untracked test has a nested class name with $, which might cause issues. It seems like it could be better to refine our approach by using the existing `org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCDriver` for a simpler solution. I want to ensure we improve our coverage, but the current test generates unwanted metadata.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining test execution**\\n\\nI'm considering how tests should run under Native Image with metadata from the agent. Dynamic class loading of the app class at build time is supported, but having $ in rule names seems suspicious. Maybe I could create a top-level public helper in a separate file? \\n\\nHowever, it appears the one-to-one mapping indicates that helper files aren't considered test classes. Though, \\\"Create/update tests only\\\" might allow for a test source file. But the rule suggests no extra generated test class files can exist.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_U0UOEczGTPFjLviyfgfQHS98|fc_0413721a0db94a26016a1188e40450819fbebbfd7edc35a8fa", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/ConnectionDialogTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "public class ConnectionDialogTest {\n    private static final String DRIVER_CLASS_NAME = ConnectionDialogTestDriver.class.getName();\n\n    @AfterEach\n    void closeDatabaseManagerWindows() {\n        closeOpenWindows();\n    }\n", "newText": "public class ConnectionDialogTest implements Driver {\n    private static final String DRIVER_CLASS_NAME = ConnectionDialogTest.class.getName();\n    private static final String URL_PREFIX = \"jdbc:connectiondialog:\";\n    private static final AtomicInteger CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\n    private static final AtomicInteger CONNECT_INVOCATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\n\n    static {\n        try {\n            DriverManager.registerDriver(new ConnectionDialogTest(false));\n        } catch (SQLException exception) {\n            throw new ExceptionInInitializerError(exception);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public ConnectionDialogTest() {\n        this(true);\n    }\n\n    private ConnectionDialogTest(boolean countInvocation) {\n        if (countInvocation) {\n            CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.incrementAndGet();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @AfterEach\n    void closeDatabaseManagerWindows() {\n        closeOpenWindows();\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "        String dialogUrl = ConnectionDialogTestDriver.URL_PREFIX + realUrl;\n        ConnectionDialogTestDriver.reset();\n", "newText": "        String dialogUrl = URL_PREFIX + realUrl;\n        resetDriverInvocations();\n"}, {"oldText": "        assertThat(ConnectionDialogTestDriver.constructorInvocations()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(ConnectionDialogTestDriver.connectInvocations()).isEqualTo(1);\n", "newText": "        assertThat(CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS).hasValue(1);\n        assertThat(CONNECT_INVOCATIONS).hasValue(1);\n"}, {"oldText": "    public static final class ConnectionDialogTestDriver implements Driver {\n        static final String URL_PREFIX = \"jdbc:connectiondialog:\";\n        private static final AtomicInteger CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\n        private static final AtomicInteger CONNECT_INVOCATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\n\n        static {\n            try {\n                DriverManager.registerDriver(new ConnectionDialogTestDriver(false));\n            } catch (SQLException exception) {\n                throw new ExceptionInInitializerError(exception);\n            }\n        }\n\n        public ConnectionDialogTestDriver() {\n            this(true);\n        }\n\n        private ConnectionDialogTestDriver(boolean countInvocation) {\n            if (countInvocation) {\n                CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.incrementAndGet();\n            }\n        }\n\n        static void reset() {\n            CONSTRUCTOR_INVOCATIONS.set(0);\n            CONNECT_INVOCATIONS.set(0);\n        }\n\n     